In the sixth episode of our podcast series: ‘In First Person’ we follow the story of Tumi Moilwa, a nurse who was abducted and forced to endure 10 days in a car boot, gagged and blindfolded without food and water. She had been working in Scotland, in the UK, at the time of the incident. What happens when one goes through a traumatic experience that changes their lives forever? In the audio below, Tumi opens up about her experience and how it changed her life:  *Tumi Moilwa – not her real name*